1
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:03,100
(Previously)
Gaysorn, from now on,

2
00:00:03,101 --> 00:00:05,000
I won't let anything hurt you ever again.

3
00:00:05,100 --> 00:00:06,100
Trust me.

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,800
Last night, Gaysorn's
fragrance filled the entire house.

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,300
How are we going to extract it?

6
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:17,900
I need clothes with more
of Gaysorn's scent on them.

7
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,400
Come on!

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:22,000
The faster your heart beats,
the more you'll sweat.

9
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,500
Hey, you! Let me wipe it for you.

10
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:36,699
I also want to know...

11
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:41,900
why Mr. Scent had Kusuma's staff
collect Gaysorn's sweat-wiped cloth.

12
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,301
Damn it!

13
00:01:34,065 --> 00:01:36,908
Why can't I make it? Why?

14
00:01:54,348 --> 00:01:55,505
Please eat something.

15
00:01:56,478 --> 00:01:57,678
I'm not hungry yet.

16
00:01:59,724 --> 00:02:00,725
Hey.

17
00:02:02,225 --> 00:02:03,585
It's been four years already.

18
00:02:04,817 --> 00:02:07,585
It's been four years of you
trying to come up with the Bussaba scent.

19
00:02:07,929 --> 00:02:10,249
You've been hidden in this lab
and not going anywhere else.

20
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:12,743
Our company is in trouble
when nobody is looking after it.

21
00:02:12,804 --> 00:02:14,505
Also your son is about to go to school.

22
00:02:15,005 --> 00:02:18,505
What? You can't handle that?

23
00:02:19,972 --> 00:02:22,073
When I can bring back the Bussaba scent,

24
00:02:22,478 --> 00:02:23,945
everything will get better.

25
00:02:24,516 --> 00:02:25,517
Come on.

26
00:02:27,327 --> 00:02:28,328
I told you

27
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:31,665
when we can bring back the s…scen…

28
00:02:33,801 --> 00:02:34,985
Hey!

29
00:02:35,892 --> 00:02:36,893
Hey!

30
00:02:39,350 --> 00:02:40,351
Hey!

31
00:02:44,721 --> 00:02:45,722
Hey!

32
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:51,365
Who's there? Come here and help!

33
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:14,000
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 5)

34
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:21,386
This?

35
00:04:22,036 --> 00:04:23,037
Give it to me.

36
00:04:24,005 --> 00:04:26,625
This is a cloth to wipe your sweat,
you remember?

37
00:04:29,265 --> 00:04:30,668
Why is it in the bag?

38
00:04:32,234 --> 00:04:33,236
Let's go.

39
00:04:33,465 --> 00:04:34,585
Wait.

40
00:04:35,711 --> 00:04:36,969
I am as curious as he is.

41
00:04:37,624 --> 00:04:40,258
Why do you ask a courier from Kusuma

42
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:42,703
to come and collect this
with Gaysorn's sweat on it?

43
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:47,025
What are you trying to do?

44
00:04:58,247 --> 00:04:59,345
Why did you do that?

45
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:04,611
Are you a pervert?

46
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:07,682
I don't think so.

47
00:05:08,276 --> 00:05:10,145
I can answer it for him since I'm his ex.

48
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:12,940
He never collects
anything from his boyfriend,

49
00:05:13,889 --> 00:05:14,890
he didn't even care.

50
00:05:25,465 --> 00:05:27,065
What is your plan exactly?

51
00:05:27,817 --> 00:05:28,818
Scent?

52
00:05:32,575 --> 00:05:33,576
What is it?

53
00:05:36,937 --> 00:05:38,185
I need an explanation.

54
00:05:45,209 --> 00:05:47,465
Fine, I will tell you.

55
00:05:50,946 --> 00:05:52,978
But you two can't tell anyone about this,

56
00:05:53,484 --> 00:05:54,485
okay?

57
00:06:02,192 --> 00:06:04,272
I just want to extract your
scent to make a perfume.

58
00:06:04,713 --> 00:06:05,714
Huh?

59
00:06:06,239 --> 00:06:07,240
Hey,

60
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:11,065
I'm sorry for not telling you sooner.

61
00:06:11,583 --> 00:06:12,985
We'll talk at home.

62
00:06:14,305 --> 00:06:15,306
Give it to me.

63
00:06:19,988 --> 00:06:20,989
Gaysorn!

64
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,521
Gaysorn.

65
00:07:04,976 --> 00:07:06,885
Gaysorn.

66
00:07:07,968 --> 00:07:08,969
Please listen to me.

67
00:07:23,845 --> 00:07:25,545
I have a reason for doing this.

68
00:07:27,392 --> 00:07:28,393
Do you remember

69
00:07:29,109 --> 00:07:31,405
that you said you would go home
after finding your mom?

70
00:07:37,152 --> 00:07:38,592
I've thought about it and I realized

71
00:07:39,541 --> 00:07:42,125
I couldn't live without your scent.

72
00:07:55,693 --> 00:07:57,445
I want to preserve your scent

73
00:07:58,275 --> 00:07:59,276
and that's it.

74
00:08:04,473 --> 00:08:06,245
You don't have to do that.

75
00:08:08,211 --> 00:08:09,212
I wont do it anymore.

76
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,445
If you don't like it, then I won't do it.

77
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:16,005
I don't know how long
we'll stay together like this.

78
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:19,268
I want to see you smile,

79
00:08:20,268 --> 00:08:21,269
I want to see you laugh,

80
00:08:23,085 --> 00:08:25,565
I want our memories will
be filled with good feelings.

81
00:08:35,496 --> 00:08:36,525
Please forgive me.

82
00:09:06,709 --> 00:09:07,710
Hey,

83
00:09:10,104 --> 00:09:11,125
you said that

84
00:09:12,005 --> 00:09:14,405
you didn't know how long
we would stay together.

85
00:09:16,147 --> 00:09:17,365
If you can choose,

86
00:09:18,611 --> 00:09:20,125
how long would you like me to stay?

87
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:25,065
I don't know.

88
00:09:26,154 --> 00:09:27,565
I don't want you to go anywhere.

89
00:09:29,571 --> 00:09:31,772
I want keep smelling your scent like this.

90
00:09:37,269 --> 00:09:39,205
You don't have to develop
a perfume of my scent.

91
00:09:41,616 --> 00:09:43,005
Women from Mudan

92
00:09:44,345 --> 00:09:45,346
will gradually

93
00:09:46,821 --> 00:09:49,205
lose their scents when they're pregnant.

94
00:09:53,264 --> 00:09:54,544
On the contrary, scents from men

95
00:09:56,081 --> 00:09:57,775
will continue to be like this

96
00:09:59,189 --> 00:10:00,485
until we are old.

97
00:10:05,175 --> 00:10:07,725
Then I will keep smelling
you until you're old.

98
00:10:20,045 --> 00:10:21,125
Pinky swear for making up.

99
00:11:29,515 --> 00:11:30,516
Gaysorn.

100
00:11:31,317 --> 00:11:34,085
I will keep searching for your mom for you,

101
00:11:35,307 --> 00:11:36,685
No matter how long it takes,

102
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,885
I will find her for you.

103
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,081
Thank you.

104
00:13:37,173 --> 00:13:39,485
My brain is fried after
smelling so many perfumes.

105
00:13:42,283 --> 00:13:43,284
My phone?

106
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:44,521
Where is it?

107
00:13:54,251 --> 00:13:55,252
Scent?

108
00:13:56,251 --> 00:13:57,365
What voice messages?

109
00:13:59,765 --> 00:14:00,766
Sun,

110
00:14:01,285 --> 00:14:03,205
Gaysorn found out about
us developing a perfume.

111
00:14:03,595 --> 00:14:04,675
And he is not fine with it.

112
00:14:05,099 --> 00:14:06,425
So I decided

113
00:14:06,842 --> 00:14:08,693
not to continue with Mudan scent.

114
00:14:09,452 --> 00:14:11,412
I'm sorry that you've
spent so much time on this.

115
00:14:11,608 --> 00:14:12,648
You can abort the mission.

116
00:14:13,085 --> 00:14:14,285
I will talk to Uncle about it.

117
00:14:15,288 --> 00:14:16,290
What did he say?

118
00:14:17,765 --> 00:14:18,766
Uncle?

119
00:14:19,283 --> 00:14:20,365
What did Scent say?

120
00:14:22,109 --> 00:14:23,923
He sent voice messages.

121
00:14:24,437 --> 00:14:26,645
- Well, call him back!
- Okay, okay.

122
00:14:35,725 --> 00:14:36,726
I…

123
00:14:37,749 --> 00:14:39,750
He turned off his phone.

124
00:14:40,205 --> 00:14:41,285
It can't be.

125
00:14:41,931 --> 00:14:44,765
We promised the investors
to launch the new scent.

126
00:14:48,565 --> 00:14:49,834
Uncle… look.

127
00:14:50,685 --> 00:14:52,645
I prepared a few scents just in case.

128
00:14:55,650 --> 00:14:57,805
Nothing can beat the scent from the Mudan.

129
00:14:58,945 --> 00:14:59,946
Damn it!

130
00:15:17,795 --> 00:15:18,796
What are you cooking?

131
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,086
I'm cooking soup.

132
00:15:27,515 --> 00:15:28,565
You know how?

133
00:15:29,493 --> 00:15:30,694
I'm watching the clip.

134
00:15:35,445 --> 00:15:36,446
Can I help you?

135
00:15:37,179 --> 00:15:38,180
It's fine.

136
00:15:39,611 --> 00:15:41,685
- Ow!
- Be careful.

137
00:15:45,877 --> 00:15:47,878
I think it's easier to buy the soup.

138
00:15:51,045 --> 00:15:52,046
Nope.

139
00:15:52,736 --> 00:15:55,621
We're living together
and I want to help you out.

140
00:16:23,925 --> 00:16:25,805
How is it? Is it good?

141
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,721
So good.

142
00:16:28,021 --> 00:16:29,627
This is chef-cooking level.

143
00:16:29,904 --> 00:16:30,905
Really?

144
00:16:31,995 --> 00:16:32,996
Really.

145
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:45,045
I will check on that, you should rest.

146
00:16:51,379 --> 00:16:52,925
You left me such dangerous messages

147
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:54,117
and then you turned off your phone?

148
00:16:54,141 --> 00:16:55,285
How could you do that to me?

149
00:16:56,277 --> 00:16:58,204
So you came all the way
to my house to call me out?

150
00:16:58,229 --> 00:16:59,130
Damn right I am!

151
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:01,605
You told me to abort the mission
and you left me a bomb.

152
00:17:01,746 --> 00:17:03,546
You told me that you
would talk to you uncle.

153
00:17:04,221 --> 00:17:06,419
Hey, I said that I would talk to him,

154
00:17:06,632 --> 00:17:08,411
- which means that I am about to…
- No, you can't.

155
00:17:08,435 --> 00:17:10,205
You have to talk to him now.

156
00:17:10,317 --> 00:17:11,445
He is so furious.

157
00:17:11,485 --> 00:17:13,325
I've never seen him
being this furious before.

158
00:17:14,325 --> 00:17:15,326
Are you sure?

159
00:17:15,726 --> 00:17:17,805
I am dead serious.

160
00:17:27,197 --> 00:17:28,198
Hey.

161
00:17:28,765 --> 00:17:29,766
Who's here?

162
00:17:30,259 --> 00:17:32,803
It's Sun. He needed to run
some errands but he left.

163
00:17:34,627 --> 00:17:36,005
Are you tried of the city view?

164
00:17:39,008 --> 00:17:40,009
Why did you ask me?

165
00:17:40,597 --> 00:17:41,837
Do you want to look at the sea?

166
00:17:42,507 --> 00:17:43,508
The sea?

167
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:45,130
That's right.

168
00:17:45,227 --> 00:17:47,005
The sea, like I showed you the picture of.

169
00:17:47,234 --> 00:17:49,191
Really? I do.

170
00:17:49,686 --> 00:17:51,216
Let's go. We should go now.

171
00:17:58,752 --> 00:18:00,005
Why do we have to hurry?

172
00:18:02,616 --> 00:18:03,965
So we will get there faster.

173
00:18:13,224 --> 00:18:14,225
Scent.

174
00:18:15,139 --> 00:18:16,140
Uncle?

175
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:24,005
- I'm about to…
- Is this Gaysorn?

176
00:18:30,621 --> 00:18:32,145
I have something to talk to him about.

177
00:18:42,045 --> 00:18:43,605
I will get straight to the point.

178
00:18:45,309 --> 00:18:46,685
Did you know that

179
00:18:47,090 --> 00:18:49,901
Scent wanted to develop your scent?

180
00:18:53,608 --> 00:18:54,707
I told you

181
00:18:55,032 --> 00:18:56,325
that he wasn't okay with that.

182
00:18:56,627 --> 00:18:57,827
We won't continue the project.

183
00:18:58,136 --> 00:18:59,137
Why's that?

184
00:18:59,619 --> 00:19:01,419
What about your dad?
What are you going to do?

185
00:19:01,797 --> 00:19:02,798
Uncle?

186
00:19:05,312 --> 00:19:07,325
Don't you feel sorry for his dad?

187
00:19:09,152 --> 00:19:11,325
Does my scent have
something to do with him?

188
00:19:12,013 --> 00:19:13,014
Well…

189
00:19:13,016 --> 00:19:14,456
You should leave my dad out of this.

190
00:19:18,259 --> 00:19:19,260
Why?

191
00:19:19,496 --> 00:19:22,125
If Gaysorn realizes
how bad your dad's condition is,

192
00:19:23,016 --> 00:19:24,565
I'm sure he will help us.

193
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:31,965
What's wrong with Scent's dad?

194
00:19:48,549 --> 00:19:49,550
You should leave.

195
00:19:53,085 --> 00:19:54,086
How are you?

196
00:19:59,675 --> 00:20:00,725
This is Scent's dad,

197
00:20:01,056 --> 00:20:02,485
he is my older brother.

198
00:20:06,494 --> 00:20:08,998
His dad tried to develop a
perfume with the Mudan scent.

199
00:20:09,637 --> 00:20:11,145
But he couldn't succeed.

200
00:20:12,485 --> 00:20:15,845
He was so stressed,
he couldn't eat or sleep

201
00:20:17,827 --> 00:20:19,325
until he got a stroke.

202
00:20:20,153 --> 00:20:21,398
And he became like this.

203
00:20:27,371 --> 00:20:29,936
We thought that if Dad could
smell Mudan's scent again,

204
00:20:30,757 --> 00:20:32,485
he would recover and be back to normal.

205
00:20:34,517 --> 00:20:35,605
You think it's possible.

206
00:20:39,994 --> 00:20:40,995
Hey.

207
00:20:42,037 --> 00:20:43,200
This is Scent's friend.

208
00:20:44,016 --> 00:20:45,445
He is from Mudan.

209
00:20:47,915 --> 00:20:49,885
He has the same scent that you want.

210
00:20:50,288 --> 00:20:51,290
Do you remember?

211
00:20:52,525 --> 00:20:53,526
It is the scent

212
00:20:54,526 --> 00:20:56,895
that is more fragrant than
all of flowers in this world.

213
00:21:27,544 --> 00:21:28,984
- Dad?
- What?

214
00:21:29,545 --> 00:21:30,546
Hey!

215
00:21:30,605 --> 00:21:31,606
Dad?

216
00:21:32,776 --> 00:21:33,777
Bro?

217
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:34,961
What is wrong with him?

218
00:21:35,224 --> 00:21:36,245
- Dad?
- What?

219
00:21:37,416 --> 00:21:38,417
What is wrong with him?

220
00:21:38,616 --> 00:21:40,405
I don't know. He's never been like this.

221
00:21:41,352 --> 00:21:42,353
Hey!

222
00:21:43,973 --> 00:21:44,974
- Hey!
- Dad?

223
00:21:45,968 --> 00:21:47,680
Everyone, please leave.

224
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:48,991
Please wait outside.

225
00:21:49,669 --> 00:21:50,370
Dad?

226
00:21:50,469 --> 00:21:52,245
- Please leave, everyone.
- Dad?

227
00:21:53,099 --> 00:21:54,965
Wait outside, please.

228
00:21:55,291 --> 00:21:56,292
Please, just go.

229
00:22:02,987 --> 00:22:04,725
Sir, you need to breathe slowly.

230
00:22:06,752 --> 00:22:07,753
Sir?

231
00:22:09,898 --> 00:22:12,205
You need to breathe slowly, okay?

232
00:22:14,467 --> 00:22:15,468
Okay?

233
00:22:15,736 --> 00:22:17,805
Breathe in, breathe out, slowly.

234
00:22:23,869 --> 00:22:25,405
Why didn't you tell me about it?

235
00:22:28,162 --> 00:22:29,163
I didn't want to tell you

236
00:22:29,949 --> 00:22:31,869
because I didn't want
to use it to pressure you.

237
00:22:34,473 --> 00:22:35,725
But now I know.

238
00:22:38,227 --> 00:22:40,488
If you're not okay with
it, don't mind my uncle.

239
00:22:41,448 --> 00:22:44,085
You have power over your
own scent and body.

240
00:22:57,445 --> 00:22:59,205
I don't want to make
you feel uncomfortable.

241
00:23:37,976 --> 00:23:39,595
- Hello.
- Hello.

242
00:23:40,288 --> 00:23:41,688
First of all, I would like to thank

243
00:23:41,725 --> 00:23:43,605
all of the representatives
for joining the event.

244
00:23:44,104 --> 00:23:46,125
Kusuma is a small company,

245
00:23:46,528 --> 00:23:49,445
we're lucky that we can produce
perfumes which people love.

246
00:23:51,628 --> 00:23:54,785
We produced only 100
bottles of the Bussaba perfume.

247
00:23:55,134 --> 00:23:57,005
Many of you might be wondering

248
00:23:57,108 --> 00:23:59,525
why we produced only 100 bottles.

249
00:24:00,131 --> 00:24:01,132
It is because

250
00:24:01,528 --> 00:24:03,968
the perfume is developed
from its confidential signature scent

251
00:24:04,189 --> 00:24:06,496
so we can produce only 100 bottles.

252
00:24:07,077 --> 00:24:08,445
More importantly,

253
00:24:09,015 --> 00:24:11,685
we will never develop this
type of scent in the future.

254
00:24:13,307 --> 00:24:16,005
If you take a look inside the envelope,

255
00:24:16,052 --> 00:24:17,652
you will smell the sample of this scent.

256
00:24:17,965 --> 00:24:20,965
We'd like you to experience how fragrant

257
00:24:21,448 --> 00:24:22,449
Bussaba can be.

258
00:24:23,272 --> 00:24:24,273
Please try.

259
00:24:32,861 --> 00:24:34,245
It smells so nice.

260
00:24:34,381 --> 00:24:36,805
I've never smelled
anything this nice before.

261
00:25:08,827 --> 00:25:10,725
Now, I'd like to introduce all of you

262
00:25:10,805 --> 00:25:12,806
to auction our new perfume.

263
00:25:13,325 --> 00:25:16,045
The auction session begins right now.

264
00:25:16,091 --> 00:25:17,131
The starting price will be

265
00:25:17,251 --> 00:25:18,552
50,000 baht.

266
00:25:21,176 --> 00:25:24,445
Every bid will move
up at least 10,000 baht.

267
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,765
The auction will start now.

268
00:25:27,832 --> 00:25:28,833
60,000?

269
00:25:30,099 --> 00:25:31,885
70,000? 80,000?

270
00:25:32,157 --> 00:25:33,245
90,000?

271
00:25:33,517 --> 00:25:35,085
100,000?

272
00:25:35,352 --> 00:25:36,965
110,000?

273
00:25:37,285 --> 00:25:39,125
- 200,000
- 200,000?

274
00:25:40,093 --> 00:25:41,605
300,000?

275
00:25:42,125 --> 00:25:43,365
It is 300,000 baht already.

276
00:25:43,667 --> 00:25:44,805
400,000?

277
00:25:44,933 --> 00:25:46,245
410,000?

278
00:25:46,765 --> 00:25:48,005
500,000?

279
00:25:48,101 --> 00:25:50,725
Does anybody want to bid more than this?
500,000 baht going once?

280
00:25:58,827 --> 00:25:59,828
How was he?

281
00:25:59,872 --> 00:26:02,485
He's fine. He was just too excited earlier.

282
00:26:10,093 --> 00:26:11,925
You're not the only one who got excited.

283
00:26:13,021 --> 00:26:14,565
I was so excited too.

284
00:26:18,994 --> 00:26:21,365
Please wait, it won't be long

285
00:26:22,083 --> 00:26:23,723
for our company to make a great comeback.

286
00:27:11,053 --> 00:27:12,054
Hey,

287
00:27:14,232 --> 00:27:15,233
let's go.

288
00:27:15,525 --> 00:27:16,526
Where to?

289
00:27:18,024 --> 00:27:19,365
Come on, let's go.

290
00:28:10,667 --> 00:28:11,668
Is it pretty?

291
00:28:13,179 --> 00:28:14,180
It is.

292
00:28:15,485 --> 00:28:16,486
So pretty.

293
00:28:18,907 --> 00:28:20,365
Thank you for taking me here.

294
00:28:28,096 --> 00:28:29,097
What?

295
00:28:29,627 --> 00:28:31,145
What are you doing?

296
00:28:31,685 --> 00:28:33,445
This is what we do
when we are at the beach.

297
00:28:37,699 --> 00:28:38,965
You want to start a fight?

298
00:28:39,286 --> 00:28:41,082
- You really want to?
- Hey!

299
00:28:42,613 --> 00:28:44,101
Is it how we do it?

300
00:29:24,885 --> 00:29:25,886
There are so many

301
00:29:26,458 --> 00:29:28,145
beautiful places in this world.

302
00:29:29,485 --> 00:29:30,795
I will take you to them.

303
00:29:50,768 --> 00:29:52,128
You're releasing your scent again.

304
00:30:45,003 --> 00:30:46,004
From now on,

305
00:30:47,645 --> 00:30:49,446
you are my whole world.

306
00:30:54,101 --> 00:30:55,765
You are my whole world, too.

307
00:32:16,301 --> 00:32:17,302
Scent,

308
00:32:18,923 --> 00:32:20,125
about your dad.

309
00:32:22,667 --> 00:32:24,285
- Do you want me to...?
- It's fine.

310
00:32:26,571 --> 00:32:28,165
I've been thinking about it.

311
00:32:29,752 --> 00:32:30,925
My dad became like this

312
00:32:30,945 --> 00:32:32,832
because he was obsessed with the Mudan scent.

313
00:32:34,512 --> 00:32:36,395
If he smells the scent again,

314
00:32:37,707 --> 00:32:39,205
his condition could get worse.

315
00:32:44,579 --> 00:32:46,859
Where did your dad smell the scent
of the Mudan people from?

316
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:52,981
Our company launched a
product with the Mudan scent.

317
00:32:54,451 --> 00:32:56,085
Mudan-scented perfume?

318
00:32:57,352 --> 00:32:58,353
That's right.

319
00:32:59,805 --> 00:33:01,005
I was so young.

320
00:33:01,579 --> 00:33:02,945
But I remember that

321
00:33:03,035 --> 00:33:06,345
it was the scent that
ignited the company to be well-known

322
00:33:06,709 --> 00:33:07,710
until now.

323
00:33:09,845 --> 00:33:10,846
I don't think

324
00:33:11,846 --> 00:33:13,696
we called it Mudan perfume back then.

325
00:33:15,242 --> 00:33:16,293
I think Dad called it

326
00:33:16,827 --> 00:33:17,828
Bussaba perfume.

327
00:33:21,445 --> 00:33:22,805
Bussaba perfume?

328
00:33:40,243 --> 00:33:42,923
Where did you get the idea
that Busaba was taken from a person's name?

329
00:33:43,085 --> 00:33:44,365
It must be from a person.

330
00:33:48,696 --> 00:33:50,405
I have no idea, I didn't come up with it.

331
00:33:51,485 --> 00:33:52,565
Then who did?

332
00:33:53,811 --> 00:33:56,445
If they could smell the
scent from the Mudan people,

333
00:33:56,734 --> 00:33:58,555
it meant that they must've been close to the group.

334
00:33:58,885 --> 00:34:00,725
They could be the one
coming up with the name.

335
00:34:08,277 --> 00:34:09,278
Pruek.

336
00:34:10,987 --> 00:34:13,045
Pruek came up with the name.

337
00:34:14,197 --> 00:34:15,198
Pruek?

338
00:34:16,923 --> 00:34:17,924
That's right.

339
00:34:18,277 --> 00:34:19,945
He was the company's perfumer

340
00:34:21,133 --> 00:34:22,805
who developed the Busaba scent.

341
00:34:23,789 --> 00:34:24,885
Where is he now?

342
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:29,565
Pruek is dead.

343
00:34:34,925 --> 00:34:36,126
How did he die?

344
00:34:47,685 --> 00:34:48,886
He fell down the stairs.

345
00:34:52,525 --> 00:34:55,526
I couldn't help him when I saw his body.

346
00:34:57,845 --> 00:34:59,046
That's so sad.

347
00:35:00,064 --> 00:35:01,065
What about the others?

348
00:35:02,037 --> 00:35:03,397
Did you see him with someone else?

349
00:35:05,573 --> 00:35:06,574
I heard that

350
00:35:07,946 --> 00:35:10,205
he was in a fight with his wife

351
00:35:10,378 --> 00:35:11,861
and his wife disappeared.

352
00:35:44,869 --> 00:35:45,870
Hey,

353
00:35:50,176 --> 00:35:51,177
what's on your mind?

354
00:35:55,162 --> 00:35:57,595
Hey, calm down.

355
00:35:59,253 --> 00:36:00,254
Don't lose hope.

356
00:36:03,732 --> 00:36:05,045
I don't know…

357
00:36:07,520 --> 00:36:09,245
I got this from the HR department.

358
00:36:12,261 --> 00:36:13,262
What is it?

359
00:36:16,029 --> 00:36:18,253
Here. This is Pruek.

360
00:36:25,585 --> 00:36:27,416
If he could smell my mom,

361
00:36:29,315 --> 00:36:30,725
it meant that he could be my dad.

362
00:36:32,645 --> 00:36:33,646
Do you want to prove it?

363
00:36:36,104 --> 00:36:37,105
How?

364
00:36:38,376 --> 00:36:39,485
I also got this.

365
00:36:41,782 --> 00:36:42,805
It's his address.

366
00:37:24,994 --> 00:37:27,085
But it looks like it's been
abandoned for so long.

367
00:37:53,285 --> 00:37:54,325
Look at this house,

368
00:37:55,605 --> 00:37:57,165
I'm not sure if we can find anything.

369
00:37:59,990 --> 00:38:01,017
We can try to look.

370
00:40:18,669 --> 00:40:19,670
That's him.

371
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:25,085
So this is his house for sure.

372
00:40:37,357 --> 00:40:38,358
Look.

373
00:40:39,363 --> 00:40:40,364
Look at this.

374
00:40:46,976 --> 00:40:47,977
Mom.

375
00:40:55,992 --> 00:40:56,993
See that?

376
00:40:57,784 --> 00:40:58,785
That's you.

377
00:41:01,581 --> 00:41:02,582
What do you mean?

378
00:41:04,333 --> 00:41:05,845
The photo that your mom held

379
00:41:06,545 --> 00:41:08,505
was a picture of you when
you were inside of her.

380
00:41:11,165 --> 00:41:13,085
So this man is really my dad?

381
00:41:14,952 --> 00:41:15,953
That's right.

382
00:41:16,354 --> 00:41:17,355
Look.

383
00:41:17,837 --> 00:41:19,885
Your mom and your dad,

384
00:41:20,643 --> 00:41:22,085
they smiled so big.

385
00:41:23,560 --> 00:41:25,045
They must be so happy to have you.

386
00:41:34,428 --> 00:41:36,365
Is this really my family?

387
00:42:11,216 --> 00:42:13,085
Not yet. Nope.

388
00:42:14,064 --> 00:42:15,445
Tell them it won't be anytime soon.

389
00:42:19,453 --> 00:42:20,725
What's going on? What's wrong?

390
00:42:21,773 --> 00:42:24,365
It's about work. What's your emergency?

391
00:42:28,125 --> 00:42:29,605
Scent and Gaysorn are still dating.

392
00:42:31,560 --> 00:42:32,685
Did you stalk them?

393
00:42:34,845 --> 00:42:36,765
Nope, I mean…

394
00:42:36,995 --> 00:42:39,285
people saw them go to the sea together.

395
00:42:40,595 --> 00:42:41,845
Gaysorn is weird.

396
00:42:42,037 --> 00:42:43,381
He knows that his
boyfriend is a pervert,

397
00:42:43,405 --> 00:42:45,365
who wants to extract his
sweat to make a perfume.

398
00:42:45,390 --> 00:42:47,451
Still, he won't break up with
him. He's not scared at all?

399
00:42:47,867 --> 00:42:49,165
Maybe they're both insane.

400
00:42:51,627 --> 00:42:52,628
But

401
00:42:53,312 --> 00:42:56,005
you think people's scent is that nice?

402
00:43:02,181 --> 00:43:03,205
I don't think so.

403
00:43:03,845 --> 00:43:06,285
Or he could use his
scent for other purposes

404
00:43:06,479 --> 00:43:08,285
so that it will smell better?

405
00:43:08,714 --> 00:43:09,715
Huh?

406
00:43:09,805 --> 00:43:12,845
You need to stop obsessing
about them already. Such nonsense.

407
00:43:15,395 --> 00:43:16,396
Wait.

408
00:43:17,396 --> 00:43:18,925
Why're you so moody?

409
00:43:20,120 --> 00:43:21,121
Come here.

410
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:23,165
Is everything okay?

411
00:43:24,136 --> 00:43:26,045
I gave an interview earlier

412
00:43:26,074 --> 00:43:28,565
about the new scents from Kusuma.

413
00:43:29,456 --> 00:43:31,456
It's been a while and we
haven't had anything yet.

414
00:43:32,165 --> 00:43:34,205
The clients are asking for new scents.

415
00:43:34,699 --> 00:43:36,379
Nobody wants to stock the old perfumes.

416
00:43:38,117 --> 00:43:39,645
I've asked them so many times

417
00:43:40,858 --> 00:43:42,858
and they said that they
couldn't provide the date.

418
00:43:54,365 --> 00:43:55,366
Hey,

419
00:43:56,123 --> 00:43:57,403
why don't you ask them directly?

420
00:43:58,883 --> 00:43:59,884
Ask who?

421
00:44:26,976 --> 00:44:28,087
Mekin? What the hell?

422
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:30,325
What's going on? Hey!

423
00:44:34,453 --> 00:44:35,893
Ray, are you crazy? What's going on?

424
00:44:45,755 --> 00:44:47,085
My dad isn't here anymore.

425
00:44:52,170 --> 00:44:53,765
And I don't know where Mom is.

426
00:45:04,485 --> 00:45:06,765
We will find your mom no matter what.

427
00:45:13,781 --> 00:45:14,782
But…

428
00:45:16,285 --> 00:45:17,485
Mudan people

429
00:45:20,005 --> 00:45:21,685
won't leave their mates,

430
00:45:25,285 --> 00:45:26,485
unless…

431
00:45:28,803 --> 00:45:29,804
Hey,

432
00:45:30,931 --> 00:45:32,571
stop with your negative thoughts already.

433
00:45:41,512 --> 00:45:43,545
What if she's already dead?

434
00:45:49,754 --> 00:45:50,855
Listen to me,

435
00:45:53,056 --> 00:45:54,645
even if you have nobody left,

436
00:45:57,176 --> 00:45:58,285
you still have me.

437
00:45:59,725 --> 00:46:01,285
I will be right by your side.

438
00:46:02,323 --> 00:46:03,485
I'll be with you,

439
00:46:04,589 --> 00:46:05,685
when you laugh,

440
00:46:07,590 --> 00:46:08,686
or when you cry.

441
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:13,041
I promise you that.

442
00:46:17,544 --> 00:46:18,545
Thank you.

443
00:46:21,960 --> 00:46:24,405
But you told me that

444
00:46:25,165 --> 00:46:26,645
Mudan people

445
00:46:26,952 --> 00:46:29,005
will not leave their mate,

446
00:46:29,605 --> 00:46:30,805
when they find them.

447
00:46:32,093 --> 00:46:33,094
Is that true?

448
00:47:31,445 --> 00:47:32,925
Tawan.

449
00:47:37,658 --> 00:47:38,765
I want you to have this.

450
00:47:46,202 --> 00:47:47,325
Duen?

451
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:51,205
You gave my nephew a silver bracelet,

452
00:47:51,325 --> 00:47:54,345
does your dad know about this?

453
00:47:55,037 --> 00:47:57,705
That's like you're proposing to him.

454
00:48:01,053 --> 00:48:02,645
(In unison) Let's get married.

455
00:48:06,200 --> 00:48:08,565
(In unison) A girl asked
Tawan to marry her.

456
00:48:12,680 --> 00:48:13,681
Tawan.

457
00:48:15,005 --> 00:48:16,885
Duen will be sad if you leave it like that.

458
00:48:17,666 --> 00:48:18,667
You should keep it.

459
00:48:23,906 --> 00:48:25,907
Mata, please give it back to her dad.

460
00:48:26,285 --> 00:48:28,085
I won't accept a silver
bracelet from anyone,

461
00:48:28,464 --> 00:48:29,465
except

462
00:48:31,003 --> 00:48:32,004
you.

463
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:35,801
Just go.

464
00:49:07,367 --> 00:49:08,514
[Call from Scent]

465
00:49:10,283 --> 00:49:11,284
Hey,

466
00:49:12,789 --> 00:49:13,790
where are you?

467
00:49:15,013 --> 00:49:16,605
I ordered us some food.

468
00:49:17,248 --> 00:49:18,605
Please set the table.

469
00:49:18,949 --> 00:49:20,669
I'll be right back to have dinner with you.

470
00:49:20,987 --> 00:49:23,325
I see. Sure.

471
00:49:25,344 --> 00:49:27,345
I have something special for you.

472
00:49:30,434 --> 00:49:32,435
And I have something special for you too.

473
00:49:34,136 --> 00:49:35,137
See you later.

474
00:49:36,346 --> 00:49:37,329
See you.

475
00:49:38,653 --> 00:49:40,005
Right?

476
00:49:46,509 --> 00:49:47,510
Yeah?

477
00:49:48,397 --> 00:49:49,398
What's up?

478
00:49:52,565 --> 00:49:53,566
I love you.

479
00:50:04,616 --> 00:50:05,725
I love you too.

480
00:50:43,128 --> 00:50:44,129
Hello.

481
00:50:44,845 --> 00:50:46,205
Can I have a bouquet of red roses?

482
00:50:46,525 --> 00:50:47,526
Sure.

483
00:51:58,066 --> 00:51:59,067
There you go.

484
00:52:18,936 --> 00:52:20,037
Why are you home so early?

485
00:53:30,642 --> 00:53:31,643
Gaysorn?

486
00:53:51,987 --> 00:53:52,988
Gaysorn?

487
00:54:17,900 --> 00:54:19,200
Is it a village?

488
00:54:19,900 --> 00:54:20,900
Yes.

489
00:54:24,700 --> 00:54:26,900
This is Mata's and Tawan's house.

490
00:54:27,900 --> 00:54:28,900
And this is my house.

491
00:54:32,300 --> 00:54:33,100
Your house?

492
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:34,200
Yes.

493
00:54:40,100 --> 00:54:42,000
Oh, then what about my house?

494
00:55:00,600 --> 00:55:02,200
Actually, this is our house.

495
00:55:06,400 --> 00:55:07,900
Can I live with you?

496
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:10,200
Please?

497
00:55:10,600 --> 00:55:13,900
Please, please, please...
let me stay with you.

498
00:55:16,900 --> 00:55:17,900
Okay.

499
00:55:20,700 --> 00:55:22,700
Then I'll help you decorate the house.

500
00:55:54,400 --> 00:55:56,600
(Next Episode)
Gaysorn, I'm really sorry.

501
00:55:57,100 --> 00:55:58,999
But there's one thing
I never lied to you about.

502
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:01,100
Our love is real, Gaysorn.

503
00:56:01,200 --> 00:56:02,800
I don't love you anymore.

504
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:04,499
My heart doesn't beat fast...

505
00:56:04,500 --> 00:56:06,400
and I don't have any
fragrance left for you.

506
00:56:11,900 --> 00:56:12,900
Are you really going?

507
00:56:12,901 --> 00:56:15,800
I'm worried about Gaysorn.
It's been more than a month already.

508
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:20,000
So that means, when my mother came down,
my father was already dead.

509
00:56:20,100 --> 00:56:22,200
Then who told your mother to come down?

510
00:56:23,400 --> 00:56:25,200
It's over between me and Gaysorn!

511
00:56:25,300 --> 00:56:27,900
No! If he wants to know
where his mother is...

512
00:56:28,000 --> 00:56:29,640
he must bring the scent back in exchange!
